OL,3,CDoctors failed to tell a father of
OL,4,Cseven he was terminally ill
OL,6,FHe was admitted to hospital in July
OL,7,F2021 with deteriorating shortness of
OL,8,Fbreath and was diagnosed with Covid-
OL,9,F19. He also had further tests.
OL,11,FA few months later in September, a
OL,12,Fjunior doctor told him there was
OL,13,Fnothing to worry about and reassured
OL,14,Fhim he would be OK, despite not having
OL,15,Fevidence that this would be true.
OL,17,FIn November, Mr Chapman was seen by a
OL,18,Fconsultant who noted in a letter to
OL,19,Fhis GP that he had pulmonary fibrosis.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/13
