OL,3,CDoctors failed to tell a father of
OL,4,Cseven he was terminally ill
OL,6,FThis condition involves a thickening
OL,7,Fand scarring of lung tissue, and it
OL,8,Fworsens over time.
OL,10,FThis makes it harder for the lungs to
OL,11,Ffunction, leading to increasing
OL,12,Fshortness of breath and a dry cough.
OL,14,FThere is no cure for the condition and
OL,15,Ftreatments can only work to relieve
OL,16,Fsymptoms and slow it down a little.
OL,18,FIn Mr Chapman's case, the consultant
OL,19,Fdid not send him a copy of the letter
OL,20,For tell him about the diagnosis as
OL,21,Fthey should have.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/13
