OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F399A1764875320
OL,3,CDoctors failed to tell a father of
OL,4,Cseven he was terminally ill
OL,6,F"By the time he was given the
OL,7,Finformation to make that decision he
OL,8,Fwas too poorly to work anyway, he was
OL,9,Fpractically bed-bound. We all lost
OL,10,Fthat time to spend together.
OL,12,F"It was such a rollercoaster. This has
OL,13,Faffected all of us and we've all lost
OL,14,Four trust in the NHS.
OL,16,F"A relative offered to pay for my dad
OL,17,Fto have treatment privately, but he
OL,18,Fhad such faith in the NHS that he
OL,19,Fturned it down.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUxD@AOU
