OL,3,CDoctors failed to tell a father of
OL,4,Cseven he was terminally ill
OL,6,F"Medical staff have a duty of care to
OL,7,Ftell patients what is really
OL,8,Fhappening. It was very traumatic for
OL,9,Fus all to lose him after being told
OL,10,Fthat he would be fine."
OL,12,FThe PHSO ruled that if Mr Chapman, who
OL,13,Fserved in the Royal Irish Rangers, had
OL,14,Fbeen told his prognosis, he would have
OL,15,Fbeen able to make informed decisions
OL,16,Fabout his health.
OL,18,FAs it was, he was not prepared when
OL,19,Flater told the extent of his condition.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@WO]
