OL,3,CDoctors failed to tell a father of
OL,4,Cseven he was terminally ill
OL,6,FThe PHSO also found hospital staff
OL,7,Ffailed to listen to Mr Chapman's
OL,8,Ffamily and there was poor or no record-
OL,9,Fkeeping of some consultations.
OL,11,FThe Countess of Chester Hospital NHS
OL,12,FFoundation Trust took over a year to
OL,13,Frespond to the family's complaint, did
OL,14,Fnot adequately investigate what
OL,15,Fhappened or acknowledge all its
OL,16,Ffailings, it said.
OL,18,FThe Trust also failed to properly
OL,19,Facknowledge the impact its failings
OL,20,Fhad on Mr Chapman and his family and
OL,21,Fto learn from what had happened.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/13
