OL,4,Cseven he was terminally ill
OL,6,FOf Mr Chapman's case, she added: "We
OL,7,Ffound some poor record keeping which
OL,8,Fcan affect a Trust's ability to
OL,9,Funderstand the impact of what happened
OL,10,Fand to take appropriate steps to
OL,11,Fprevent it from reoccurring.
OL,13,F"Poor quality investigations and
OL,14,Funacceptable delays in responding to
OL,15,Fcomplainants are issues we have
OL,16,Fhighlighted before in the NHS.
OL,26,@nD@bOUuD@AOU
